The paper discusses the polynomial method from circuit complexity, which is a common topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It also explores the connections between communication protocols and low-rank decompositions of matrices, which are relevant to data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper applies these connections to solve open problems in computational geometry (cs.CG).
